'''WMCM''' (103.3 [[FM broadcasting|FM]]) is an American [[radio station]] broadcasting a [[country music]] format simulcasting [[WBFB]]. Licensed to [[Rockland, Maine]], USA, the station serves the [[Mid Coast]] Maine area. The station is currently owned by [[Blueberry Broadcasting]].<ref> {{cite web|url=http://www.fcc.gov/fcc-bin/fmq?call=WMCM |title=WMCM Facility Record |work=United States [[Federal Communications Commission]], audio division }}</ref>
== Programming == [[File:WMCM logo.jpg|thumb|left|previous logo]]Previous to its country music format, the station was a short lived [[classical music]] format, the station signed on as a [[List of North American broadcast station classes|Class A]] on 93.5 as WRKD, sister to [[WRKD]] AM 1450, that now carries [[Fox Sports Radio]]. WMCM upgraded to 20.6 [[watt|kw]] and a frequency change to 103.3 in the late 1980s. As of September 28, 2009, it became part of a three-station country network based out of Blueberry's Bangor office, simulcasting [[WBFB]] and also heard on [[WLKE]].[http://www.fybush.com/NERW/2009/090928/nerw.html#me][http://knox.villagesoup.com/Community/story.cfm?StoryID=177087].
